09:21.594 --> 09:22.827
Anyway, last night--

09:22.829 --> 09:24.629
Last night, I was--

09:24.631 --> 09:27.132
I was a little bit
out of control, huh?

09:27.134 --> 09:29.768
Yeah. You were losing it.

09:29.770 --> 09:31.736
Yeah.

09:32.772 --> 09:33.805
Can I come in?

09:33.807 --> 09:35.540
No.

09:37.810 --> 09:39.370
What you fucking thinking?

09:42.848 --> 09:43.848
I'm sorry.

09:43.850 --> 09:45.550
What do you want?

09:48.921 --> 09:50.922
I don't know.

09:50.924 --> 09:53.158
I just want to make up.

09:56.729 --> 09:59.230
Can we just kiss
and make up now?

10:01.601 --> 10:02.601
Come on.

10:02.603 --> 10:04.135
We're good, okay?

10:04.137 --> 10:05.136
Mm-hmm.

10:05.138 --> 10:07.072
I'm good.

10:07.074 --> 10:08.173
Hmm? Yeah.

10:08.175 --> 10:11.176
You want to get a beer? Yeah?

10:11.178 --> 10:13.678
- Can I get you a beer?
- Yeah.

10:13.680 --> 10:15.647
Okay.

10:28.628 --> 10:31.730
You know I could take
all this away from you, right?

10:34.166 --> 10:36.334
Yeah. Yeah, I know that.

10:40.072 --> 10:42.807
But then what
would I do without you?

10:42.809 --> 10:45.076
I don't know. I don't know.

11:01.695 --> 11:03.428
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

11:07.300 --> 11:09.367
Oh, angel, have I ever told you

11:09.369 --> 11:11.136
how much I love making coffee?

11:11.138 --> 11:13.271
Yeah, only about
a million times.

11:13.273 --> 11:15.674
I have got it down to a science.

11:15.676 --> 11:17.842
One rounded tablespoon per cup.

11:17.844 --> 11:19.811
Not mug, cup.

11:19.813 --> 11:22.047
And I only use this tablespoon.

11:22.049 --> 11:25.083
You should throw that thing
out or at least wash it.

11:25.085 --> 11:26.317
Someone's gonna get sick.

11:26.319 --> 11:28.386
Darlin', have you
lost your mind?

11:28.388 --> 11:30.855
This here is Grammy Ev's
sterling silver,

11:30.857 --> 11:33.925
and it makes the perfect
cup, and you know it,

11:33.927 --> 11:36.961
because you love
my coffee. Admit it!

11:36.963 --> 11:38.463
I know. I know.

11:38.465 --> 11:40.699
It'd be easier just to
pour in the grounds.

11:40.701 --> 11:43.702
Well, speed's not gonna
make it turn out good.

11:43.704 --> 11:46.171
Anyway, this is an art,
believe me.

11:46.173 --> 11:48.406
You've had
your dad's coffee, right?

11:48.408 --> 11:51.142
Ugh. It's worse than Sanka.

11:51.144 --> 11:53.244
Well, hello.

11:53.246 --> 11:54.946
Look who's here. You know,

11:54.948 --> 11:57.148
some men just can't take a hint

11:57.150 --> 12:00.685
that a lady is not interested.

12:02.054 --> 12:04.089
Heh. Hey, there, Charles.

12:04.091 --> 12:05.824
Hey, Jack.

12:05.826 --> 12:07.926
Hello, sunshine.

12:07.928 --> 12:09.294
Now, Jack...

12:09.296 --> 12:10.295
She'll come around.

12:10.297 --> 12:12.263
I hope so.

12:12.265 --> 12:16.234
Is that Jack Campbell trying
to act all sweet again?

12:16.236 --> 12:18.870
Ooh. Ho ho.

12:18.872 --> 12:21.206
Now, there are
those crystal-green eyes

12:21.208 --> 12:24.943
that I have been just dreaming
about since Jacksonville.

12:24.945 --> 12:26.065
They're hazel, actually.

12:27.446 --> 12:28.813
For you, ma'am.

12:28.815 --> 12:30.815
Oh, roses. How imaginative.

12:30.817 --> 12:32.951
There you go.

12:32.953 --> 12:35.353
Boy, you are one tough cookie.

12:35.355 --> 12:37.155
You know that, sunshine?

12:37.157 --> 12:39.858
You know, you can buy me all
the flowers in California.

12:39.860 --> 12:41.726
I'm still not
going out with you.

12:43.429 --> 12:47.398
Jack, I have learned a
few things in my life.

12:47.400 --> 12:48.399
Have you, now?

12:48.401 --> 12:49.434
Oh, yeah, yeah.

12:49.436 --> 12:51.069
20 years as a hairdresser,

12:51.071 --> 12:53.371
I think, qualifies me
as an expert on people.

12:53.373 --> 12:55.073
- I like your hair.
- Three divorces,

12:55.075 --> 12:58.076
I think that qualifies
me as an expert on men.

12:58.078 --> 13:00.845
And one trucker husband
who dragged me

13:00.847 --> 13:02.847
to this shithole of a town

13:02.849 --> 13:06.184
definitely qualifies me
as an expert on truckers,

13:06.186 --> 13:08.419
so hit the road, Jack.

13:08.421 --> 13:10.221
One dance.

13:10.223 --> 13:12.290
Baby, you just
give me one dance,

13:12.292 --> 13:16.161
and I will erase every bad
thought you ever had about men.

13:16.163 --> 13:17.428
Oh, yes, I will.

13:17.430 --> 13:18.429
That's right, Charles.

13:18.431 --> 13:20.498
Ooh, like a cat.

13:20.500 --> 13:22.433
Light on my feet, baby. No.

13:22.435 --> 13:25.236
Look at these moves, huh, baby.

13:25.238 --> 13:27.372
A little dip right there.

13:27.374 --> 13:30.074
Oh, yeah, I may be stocky,

13:30.076 --> 13:33.378
but I am agile.

13:45.591 --> 13:46.591
Hi.

13:46.593 --> 13:47.992
Hi.

13:49.061 --> 13:52.831
It's a quiet night, huh?

13:52.833 --> 13:55.099
Yeah. Um...

13:55.101 --> 13:57.602
it's pretty late.

13:57.604 --> 14:00.371
Yeah.

14:00.373 --> 14:02.507
You want a cup of coffee?

14:02.509 --> 14:04.409
Sure.

14:06.045 --> 14:08.947
Half and half
with three sugars, please.

14:23.529 --> 14:25.263
It's perfect.

14:30.569 --> 14:32.370
It's really good.

14:33.105 --> 14:35.373
No, no, no. It's on the house.

14:35.375 --> 14:37.308
Oh.

14:37.310 --> 14:39.277
Thank you.

14:44.984 --> 14:46.517
Gonna go.

14:46.519 --> 14:48.086
Heh. Bye.

16:14.974 --> 16:19.143
So, did you enter that
photo contest at school?

16:19.145 --> 16:22.413
Nah. I'm still trying
to come up with a theme.

16:22.415 --> 16:25.183
Kevin always said you took
your best shots outside.

16:25.185 --> 16:27.185
I don't know. I'm not
even sure I'm gonna enter.

16:27.187 --> 16:29.320
I'm telling you, Charles.

16:29.322 --> 16:30.521
One day...

16:30.523 --> 16:32.724
- I know. Stardom.
- Stardom. Stardom.

16:32.726 --> 16:34.592
Hey, remember those--
Remember those shots

16:34.594 --> 16:37.362
you took of me
on my Harley with Kevin?

16:37.364 --> 16:38.563
Those?

16:38.565 --> 16:39.564
Oh, yeah.

16:39.566 --> 16:41.065
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

16:41.067 --> 16:42.066
I still have those.

16:42.068 --> 16:44.002
Yeah, it was--Yeah.

16:44.004 --> 16:46.537
Oh, you used to love
riding, didn't you?

16:46.539 --> 16:49.707
Oh, man, I felt alive
on my bike.

16:52.277 --> 16:55.613
Yeah, I wouldn't mind
having that feeling again.

16:59.119 --> 17:01.185
Look, I am losing fuel fast.

17:01.187 --> 17:02.220
I might just--
I'm gonna crash.

17:02.222 --> 17:03.421
Okay? Mm.

17:03.423 --> 17:05.256
Time to get you to bed, cowboy.

17:05.258 --> 17:06.656
I got him. I got him.

17:06.659 --> 17:08.092
All right. Come on.

17:08.094 --> 17:10.627
All right. Thanks.

17:10.630 --> 17:12.396
You sure you don't wanna
eat something else?

17:12.398 --> 17:13.531
- No, no. Thanks.
- All right.

17:13.532 --> 17:15.700
Good night, Charles.

17:15.702 --> 17:17.300
Night, Dad.

17:20.372 --> 17:21.672
Careful.

17:21.674 --> 17:23.407
Cold.

17:33.252 --> 17:36.487
Can you believe Jack? I'm telling
you, I can't stop thinking about him.

17:36.489 --> 17:38.523
The man just never gives up.

17:39.792 --> 17:41.359
I thought you
were done with men.

17:41.361 --> 17:43.561
Oh, I--I am, angel. I am. I am.

17:43.563 --> 17:45.296
He's not gonna fool me.
Don't worry.

17:45.298 --> 17:47.365
They're all sweet and lovey
at the beginning,

17:47.367 --> 17:49.801
and then they turn into Mr. Hyde
right before your very eyes.

17:49.803 --> 17:51.669
Well, I don't get my
hopes too high either.

17:51.671 --> 17:53.471
Oh, come on. Don't say that.

17:55.707 --> 17:57.442
What? Girls don't like me.

17:57.444 --> 17:58.576
What are you talking about?

17:58.578 --> 18:00.311
You just haven't met enough.

18:00.313 --> 18:02.080
It's too early to give up.

18:02.082 --> 18:03.748
You gotta be old
and wrinkled like me.

18:03.750 --> 18:05.783
Then you can be cynical, okay?

18:05.785 --> 18:07.318
- Okay.
- Okay.

18:07.320 --> 18:09.487
"Girls don't like me"?

18:09.489 --> 18:11.789
- Girls don't like me.
- Oh, come on.

18:11.791 --> 18:13.458
They will. Trust me.

18:13.460 --> 18:15.193
They'll knock down your door.

18:15.195 --> 18:17.161
- Right.
- They are.

18:19.231 --> 18:20.631
Yeah, right.

19:10.282 --> 19:12.750
- Hi.
- Hi.

19:12.752 --> 19:13.818
What's going on?

19:15.287 --> 19:16.554
Nothing.

19:18.657 --> 19:19.824
What's that?

19:19.826 --> 19:21.325
It's nothing. Just...

19:21.327 --> 19:23.828
Well, it looks like something.
Let me see.

19:25.597 --> 19:27.231
It's really nothing.

19:27.233 --> 19:30.134
I didn't know
you were a photographer.

19:31.203 --> 19:33.871
I'm--I'm not.

19:35.608 --> 19:38.376
It says here it's
a photography contest.

19:41.814 --> 19:44.549
It's just more
of a hobby kind of.

19:44.551 --> 19:46.584
- A hobby, huh?
- Yeah.

19:46.586 --> 19:50.555
So what are you gonna take pictures
of for your hobby contest?

19:51.957 --> 19:54.892
Well, I was thinking, um,

19:54.894 --> 19:57.628
if I do end up
entering the contest,

19:57.630 --> 20:00.398
that I would--I would do the
California lighthouses.

20:02.267 --> 20:04.702
That's cool. It's really cool.

20:05.871 --> 20:08.206
Yeah.

20:08.208 --> 20:09.974
One major problem, though.

20:09.976 --> 20:12.710
I--I really need
a ride to get there,

20:12.712 --> 20:13.978
and I can't drive, and--

20:13.980 --> 20:15.213
What if I take you?

20:16.782 --> 20:19.917
What? No, that's not
what I was driving at.

20:19.919 --> 20:21.686
I know.

20:21.688 --> 20:23.654
I want to.

20:25.224 --> 20:26.958
What about tomorrow?

20:26.960 --> 20:29.794
It's a Sunday.
I'm free during the day.

20:29.796 --> 20:31.896
Plus, I kind of
owe you one. Heh.

20:31.898 --> 20:34.232
Heh.

20:34.234 --> 20:35.399
Okay.

20:36.735 --> 20:39.270
Cool. Where do you live?

20:39.272 --> 20:42.840
Um, um...

20:42.842 --> 20:44.508
where do I live?

20:44.510 --> 20:47.812
Forest--Forest Road, the
last house on the left.

20:49.448 --> 20:51.349
Cool. I'll pick you up,
like, 11:00?

20:51.351 --> 20:53.217
Yeah. Yeah, that's perfect.

20:54.319 --> 20:55.319
Great.

20:55.321 --> 20:56.487
Great.

20:56.489 --> 20:57.722
Yeah. I'll see you at 11:00.

20:57.724 --> 20:59.690
Thank you.

21:28.821 --> 21:30.955
What kind of music you into?

21:32.558 --> 21:34.425
Oh, I don't really
listen to music too much,

21:34.427 --> 21:37.528
but I like everything.

21:37.530 --> 21:38.729
Country's pretty good.

21:38.731 --> 21:40.998
My dad played a lot of country.

21:41.000 --> 21:44.669
Sometimes I go to the Cowboy
Palace with Peg and her friends.

21:44.671 --> 21:46.504
It's that country club
down on South Street.

21:46.506 --> 21:48.005
- Yeah.
- Um...

21:48.007 --> 21:51.008
Peg knows the bouncer,
so I get in without a problem,

21:51.010 --> 21:53.511
and he didn't mind, 'cause
he knows I don't drink.

21:53.513 --> 21:54.979
You don't drink?

21:54.981 --> 21:58.349
I have enough trouble
walking when I'm sober.

21:58.351 --> 21:59.884
How old are you?

21:59.886 --> 22:01.919
17. How old are you?

22:01.921 --> 22:03.587
I just turned 18.

22:08.327 --> 22:10.461
I think country's cool.

22:10.463 --> 22:12.763
I prefer harder stuff, though.

22:12.765 --> 22:15.433
I went to a couple
of concerts with Skid

22:15.435 --> 22:18.002
before I realized he was
a complete lunatic.

22:18.004 --> 22:19.370
Yeah.

22:21.406 --> 22:22.640
Anyway...

22:31.950 --> 22:35.553
I haven't been outside in
the daytime for while.

22:35.555 --> 22:37.888
I usually like to sleep late

22:37.890 --> 22:39.623
and stay in till nighttime.

22:41.927 --> 22:44.061
Why don't you go out?

22:46.965 --> 22:48.733
I don't know.

22:48.735 --> 22:51.736
I don't want people to see me,

22:51.738 --> 22:53.704
what I look like and all.

23:04.717 --> 23:05.950
Want to take a look?

23:13.859 --> 23:16.160
Who's Kevin?

23:16.162 --> 23:17.528
My older brother.

23:17.530 --> 23:20.765
This is his camera
and his stuff.

23:20.767 --> 23:22.666
Where's Kevin now?

23:23.702 --> 23:25.669
