29:53.258 --> 29:54.758
Yes, you can.

30:16.247 --> 30:18.549
Okay.

30:19.919 --> 30:21.218
You did.

30:21.220 --> 30:22.286
Really.

30:36.835 --> 30:37.968
Whoo!

30:40.872 --> 30:42.406
I'm gonna take your picture.

30:42.408 --> 30:44.842
- No.
- Ah, come on, smile.

30:44.844 --> 30:46.376
Please don't, no.

30:46.378 --> 30:48.145
- Yeah, come on, smile.
- No, please, don't. Please.

30:48.147 --> 30:49.907
- Charles, come on.
- Stop!

31:04.429 --> 31:07.397
I think it's really cool
you're so into photography.

31:15.106 --> 31:17.541
I remember when I was a kid,

31:17.543 --> 31:21.311
after I found out that girls
didn't play for the Dodgers,

31:21.313 --> 31:25.148
I got totally into the news,

31:25.150 --> 31:27.184
and I started walking around

31:27.186 --> 31:29.920
with a tape recorder
and a microphone,

31:29.922 --> 31:33.323
interviewing my mom and dad
and my little sisters.

31:37.595 --> 31:40.063
I was really into it.

31:42.300 --> 31:45.168
I remember I wanted to be
one of those reporters

31:45.170 --> 31:46.637
that goes right into the scene

31:46.639 --> 31:48.399
of the crime or the accident.

31:50.541 --> 31:53.243
I wanted to tell
whoever was in trouble

31:53.245 --> 31:57.114
or whoever had escaped the fire

31:57.116 --> 31:59.950
or whoever's kid had disappeared

31:59.952 --> 32:02.452
that everything
was gonna be okay...

32:04.956 --> 32:07.958
that it was all gonna
be okay, you know.

32:13.431 --> 32:15.899
And what have I got now?

32:27.178 --> 32:31.014
Vicki, can I ask you
something personal?

32:31.016 --> 32:32.115
Sure.

32:39.624 --> 32:41.692
How'd you become a...

32:41.694 --> 32:43.593
Heh.

32:43.595 --> 32:45.262
Sorry, I don't know--

32:45.264 --> 32:46.730
No, it's okay.

32:46.732 --> 32:49.666
It's my life. Shit.

32:51.469 --> 32:54.137
Uh, well...

32:56.007 --> 32:59.543
my asshole father used to
like to take his bullshit out

32:59.545 --> 33:02.546
on my mom and me
and my little sisters.

33:02.548 --> 33:06.350
One day, he just disappeared,
never came back.

33:08.619 --> 33:11.755
I actually managed fine,
even when my mom

33:11.757 --> 33:14.624
was bringing a different
guy home every night.

33:16.294 --> 33:18.762
Then one boyfriend moved in,

33:18.764 --> 33:21.231
and he took a liking
to me real fast,

33:21.233 --> 33:22.466
so she kicked us out.

33:22.468 --> 33:24.368
He went his way, and I met Skid,

33:24.370 --> 33:26.010
and that's pretty much it.

33:40.651 --> 33:42.686
How come you chose
to take pictures

33:42.688 --> 33:44.755
of lighthouses for your contest?

33:44.757 --> 33:46.623
Well, one day I remembered
that Kevin and I

33:46.625 --> 33:48.392
had planned to do
a road trip one summer

33:48.394 --> 33:50.260
to photograph the
lighthouses of California.

33:52.330 --> 33:56.099
He really liked the idea of the
light guiding people home.

33:59.203 --> 34:02.706
Guess you could say my brother
liked helping people a lot.

34:04.609 --> 34:06.676
How did he die?

34:06.678 --> 34:08.145
Vietnam.

34:08.147 --> 34:11.114
Shit, that's awful.

34:11.116 --> 34:13.150
He was a hero,

34:13.152 --> 34:15.217
even won a medal.

34:15.219 --> 34:17.120
Wow.

34:22.326 --> 34:24.628
It's really cool
that you're doing

34:24.630 --> 34:26.329
this lighthouse trip with me.

34:29.266 --> 34:31.301
I think it's really cool, too.

34:44.581 --> 34:47.818
How's the project
going with Vicki?

34:47.820 --> 34:49.119
Okay, I guess.

34:49.121 --> 34:50.687
I got some good shots. Yeah?

34:50.688 --> 34:52.589
Vicki's been helping out a lot.

34:52.591 --> 34:55.759
Eh, Charles, you ask me,
I think she likes you.

34:57.395 --> 34:59.329
She just feels bad for me.

34:59.331 --> 35:00.464
Ah, come on, Charles.

35:00.466 --> 35:02.732
I see how she is with you.

35:02.734 --> 35:04.768
She likes being around you.

35:04.770 --> 35:06.336
I don't know.

35:06.338 --> 35:08.171
Sure.

35:09.607 --> 35:11.808
What grade is she in, anyway?

35:15.213 --> 35:16.713
She didn't tell you?

35:16.715 --> 35:20.684
No. We just talked about
cars and motorcycles.

35:23.254 --> 35:24.788
She works at the truck stop.

35:24.790 --> 35:28.291
What do you mean, "She
works at the truck stop"?

35:28.293 --> 35:30.894
She "works" at the truck stop.

35:34.365 --> 35:36.566
Are you okay with that?

35:36.568 --> 35:38.368
Are you okay with that?

35:40.705 --> 35:43.673
I think so.

35:43.675 --> 35:45.809
I like her.

35:48.679 --> 35:50.580
I like her, too, Charles.

36:29.187 --> 36:31.688
Stay away from him, Charles.

36:32.723 --> 36:37.227
Whoo! Whoo!

36:45.603 --> 36:47.637
It's the gimp.

36:47.639 --> 36:49.206
What's in the bag?

36:49.208 --> 36:50.340
Not your treasured camera?

36:50.342 --> 36:52.842
Oh, no.

36:53.878 --> 36:55.879
Oh, where you going, huh?

36:58.216 --> 37:00.183
Huh?

37:07.491 --> 37:09.793
Who the fuck are you?

37:09.795 --> 37:10.994
Who the fuck are you?

37:10.996 --> 37:13.430
Heh. I'm your worst nightmare.

37:13.432 --> 37:14.898
Heh.

37:14.900 --> 37:17.601
I don't think you know
me very well, do you?

37:17.603 --> 37:19.369
Let's go, Charles. Come on.

37:20.504 --> 37:23.006
Excuse me, girlie.

37:23.008 --> 37:25.875
We ain't done talking to our
friend, Charles, just yet.

37:25.877 --> 37:27.577
Right, boys?

37:27.579 --> 37:31.481
Now why don't you run along
before you get hurt?

37:35.519 --> 37:37.454
Charles is coming with me.

37:42.526 --> 37:44.166
Don't fuck with him again.

37:48.299 --> 37:50.333
I may not be the best shot,

37:50.335 --> 37:52.135
but I usually hit something.

37:52.837 --> 37:54.938
Even if it's small.

38:04.682 --> 38:06.783
That was great.

38:06.785 --> 38:09.552
That would have made
the perfect photo.

38:09.554 --> 38:12.889
You should have done your
project on high school pussies.

38:16.962 --> 38:19.029
Where'd you get the gun?

38:19.031 --> 38:20.363
From Skid.

38:21.899 --> 38:25.835
Heh. Wait. How'd you
get my dad's car?

38:25.837 --> 38:27.470
I asked.

38:33.911 --> 38:35.645
Hey, grab the wheel.

38:35.647 --> 38:37.614
What? Why?

38:37.616 --> 38:40.417
Grab the wheel.

38:40.419 --> 38:43.520
You can't drive a convertible

38:43.522 --> 38:46.656
and not stand and feel
the wind in your hair!

38:46.658 --> 38:47.824
Whoo!

38:49.428 --> 38:51.361
Wow.

38:52.963 --> 38:55.532
Okay, it's your turn.

38:55.534 --> 38:56.533
Me?

38:56.535 --> 38:58.601
Yeah. Come on.

38:58.603 --> 38:59.636
Stand up.

39:03.641 --> 39:05.508
- You can do it.
- All right.

39:09.981 --> 39:12.015
Yeah!

39:12.017 --> 39:13.783
- Raise your arms.
- I can't.

39:13.785 --> 39:15.552
Yeah, you can.

39:17.855 --> 39:19.389
Ahh!

39:19.391 --> 39:20.857
Whoo!

39:20.859 --> 39:23.493
Whoo-hoo!

39:45.950 --> 39:48.151
How long have you lived here?

39:48.153 --> 39:49.619
Like six months now.

39:49.621 --> 39:51.154
Skid set me up here.

39:51.156 --> 39:54.591
Mm, he likes to know
where he can find me.

39:59.797 --> 40:01.398
Who are they?

40:01.400 --> 40:03.767
Those are my little sisters.

40:03.769 --> 40:05.168
Cute.

40:05.170 --> 40:07.370
Yeah.

40:44.141 --> 40:45.408
Whoa.

40:47.945 --> 40:50.647
I'm--I'm so sorry.

40:50.649 --> 40:54.884
I didn't--I don't know
what I'm doing anymore.

41:25.517 --> 41:27.050
Community college is
a great place to start.

41:27.052 --> 41:29.085
I could take photography?

41:29.087 --> 41:31.447
Sure. Your photography
work, it holds promise.

41:32.957 --> 41:35.492
You think you could help me
with an admission application?

41:35.494 --> 41:36.893
Absolutely.

41:36.895 --> 41:38.862
You know, Charles,

41:38.864 --> 41:41.664
I am so thrilled that you are
starting to believe in yourself.

41:41.666 --> 41:43.766
It's just great.

41:43.768 --> 41:45.735
Thanks.

42:06.657 --> 42:09.859
You and Vicki are spending a
lot of time together, huh?

42:10.896 --> 42:12.262
Yeah.

42:12.264 --> 42:15.198
Maybe we should talk
about relationships,

42:15.200 --> 42:17.634
you know, boyfriend,
girlfriend stuff.

42:17.636 --> 42:19.202
Not now, Dad.

42:19.204 --> 42:21.004
Come on. Help me look
through these photos.

42:25.209 --> 42:26.943
Charles, we still
have to talk about

42:26.945 --> 42:28.978
what's gonna happen
when I'm gone.

42:28.980 --> 42:31.214
Wait. What do you think
of these two?

42:35.586 --> 42:37.053
I think they're great.

42:37.055 --> 42:38.688
Yeah?

42:38.690 --> 42:40.690
Yeah, these two are winners.

42:48.766 --> 42:49.899
Hey, sweetie.

42:49.901 --> 42:52.168
We were just talking about you.

42:52.170 --> 42:54.270
Were those pretty little
ears of yours burning?

42:54.272 --> 42:56.739
What were you saying?

42:56.741 --> 42:57.974
Go on.

42:57.976 --> 42:59.008
What?

43:00.978 --> 43:02.946
Well, uh, we were
all gonna go dancing

43:02.948 --> 43:04.714
tomorrow night
at the Cowboy Palace,

43:04.716 --> 43:06.249
Me, Charles, and the girls.

43:06.251 --> 43:07.850
Jack here can't make it.

43:07.852 --> 43:11.187
But, um, we all were wondering

43:11.189 --> 43:12.589
if you'd like to come along.

43:12.591 --> 43:14.657
It is so much fun.

43:14.659 --> 43:15.658
Dancing?

43:15.660 --> 43:16.893
Mm-hmm, tomorrow night.

43:20.765 --> 43:24.334
Okay, yeah. Sounds like fun.

43:24.336 --> 43:28.605
Really? That's great, huh?

43:28.607 --> 43:30.573
That'll be fun.

43:34.813 --> 43:37.180
You are a breath of fresh air.
You know that?

43:37.182 --> 43:38.181
No, thank you.

43:38.183 --> 43:39.248
This dress is adorable.

43:39.250 --> 43:40.717
You look so sweet, sugar.

43:40.719 --> 43:41.985
Thank you.

43:41.987 --> 43:43.019
Doesn't she look
beautiful, Charles?

43:43.021 --> 43:44.387
- Yeah.
- Girls,

43:44.389 --> 43:46.189
have you ever seen
such a pretty little thing?

43:46.191 --> 43:47.890
Never in my lifetime. Never.

43:47.892 --> 43:50.293
Vicki, angel, if I looked
like you 35 years ago,

43:50.295 --> 43:52.261
I would have found myself
a real man.

43:52.263 --> 43:54.397
Oh, you would have had
the pick of the bunch.

43:54.399 --> 43:57.200
It would still be
the best of a bad lot.

43:57.202 --> 44:00.136
I'd rather have that than the
slime buckets we ended up with.

44:01.306 --> 44:02.772
Uh-oh.

44:02.774 --> 44:05.341
Girls, do you hear that?

44:05.343 --> 44:07.710
Time to slow dance.

44:07.712 --> 44:09.012
Who do you guys dance with?

44:09.014 --> 44:10.680
Each other. We've
always wanted men

44:10.682 --> 44:12.348
who were as caring and
understanding as us,

44:12.350 --> 44:14.717
so half of us just
pretend to be those men.

44:14.719 --> 44:16.185
All right, who's wearing
the pants tonight?

44:16.187 --> 44:17.687
Me. I did it last week.

44:20.290 --> 44:21.391
Oh, my.

44:34.906 --> 44:36.739
For what?

44:36.741 --> 44:38.441
To dance.

44:38.443 --> 44:39.442
Me?

44:39.444 --> 44:40.810
Yes!

44:40.812 --> 44:41.811
Uh...

44:41.813 --> 44:43.012
Come on. Come with me.

44:43.014 --> 44:45.114
- Oh--
